3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"RabbitX calculates RUNE/USDT funding rates hourly using a time-weighted average premium between perpetual and spot prices. The exchange's Starknet-based architecture enables real-time rate updates with minimal computational overhead. Funding payments occur automatically through the cross-margin system, with rates typically ranging from -0.1% to +0.2% per hour during normal market conditions. Long positions pay funding when rates are positive, while shorts collect payments, creating predictable arbitrage windows."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","RUNE","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"RUNE's role as THORChain's cross-chain liquidity protocol creates unique funding rate patterns not seen in other DeFi tokens. The pair often experiences sustained positive funding during periods of high cross-chain activity, as traders maintain long exposure to capture validator rewards and liquidity provider yields."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical RUNE Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"RUNE/USDT funding rates on RabbitX have shown distinct cyclical behavior, with positive rates averaging 0.05% hourly during THORChain upgrade periods. The highest sustained rates occurred during the mainnet launch phases, reaching 0.3% hourly as speculators positioned for cross-chain volume growth. Unlike pure DeFi governance tokens, RUNE's funding correlates strongly with Bitcoin and Ethereum network congestion, as higher fees drive demand for THORChain's cross-chain swaps. Historical data shows funding rates spike during major protocol milestones, creating 24-48 hour arbitrage windows for prepared traders."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Strategy Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"RabbitX's zero gas fee structure makes RUNE funding rate arbitrage particularly attractive for smaller position sizes that would be unprofitable on Ethereum-based platforms. The hourly settlement frequency allows for rapid position adjustments based on THORChain network activity and cross-chain volume metrics. Successful arbitrageurs monitor THORChain's bonding curve dynamics and validator set changes, as these directly impact RUNE demand and subsequent funding rate premiums. The exchange's cross-margin system enables capital-efficient arbitrage by allowing RUNE positions to be hedged against other DeFi perpetuals within the same account."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Management for RUNE Positions"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"RUNE's volatility profile requires careful position sizing, as the token can experience 20-30% daily moves during protocol developments or cross-chain market stress. The limited liquidity on RabbitX compared to centralized exchanges means large positions may face significant slippage during unwinding. Traders should monitor THORChain's reserve status and node operator dynamics, as these fundamentals directly impact RUNE's price stability and funding rate sustainability. The early-stage nature of RabbitX protocol adds counterparty risk that must be weighed against the favorable fee structure and funding rate opportunities."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"How often do RUNE funding payments occur on RabbitX?","answer":"RabbitX settles RUNE/USDT funding payments every hour at the top of the hour. This frequent settlement cycle allows traders to capture short-term funding rate premiums more effectively than exchanges with 8-hour cycles."},{"question":"What drives RUNE funding rates higher than other DeFi tokens?","answer":"RUNE funding rates are driven by THORChain's cross-chain liquidity demands and validator staking yields. During periods of high cross-chain volume or protocol upgrades, speculators maintain long positions to capture ecosystem growth, creating sustained positive funding rates."},{"question":"Can I hedge RUNE positions with other assets on RabbitX?","answer":"Yes, RabbitX's cross-margin system allows you to hedge RUNE exposure using other perpetual pairs within the same account. This is particularly useful for isolating funding rate arbitrage from directional price risk."},{"question":"What are the main risks of RUNE funding arbitrage on RabbitX?","answer":"Key risks include RUNE's high volatility, RabbitX's limited liquidity compared to CEXs, and early-stage protocol risks. The exchange's smaller user base can also lead to funding rate disconnects from broader market conditions."}]}]
